        <a href="/written_statements/2003/oct/27/international-development">INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT</a>

      </div>
      <h1 class='title'>Iraq</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c52WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_52ws' title='Col. 52WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c52WS' name='column_52ws' href='#column_52ws' rel='bookmark'>52WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04779'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_247'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-ann-clwyd' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_247' title='Link to this speech by Ms Ann Clwyd' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-ann-clwyd" title="Ms Ann Clwyd">Ann Clwyd</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04779">To ask the Secretary of State for International Development how many internally displaced persons of Iraqi nationality he estimates there are in UN administered camps in countries neighbouring Iraq. [133777]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04780'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_248'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-hilary-benn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_248' title='Link to this speech by Mr Hilary Benn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-hilary-benn" title="Mr Hilary Benn">Hilary Benn</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04780">Latest estimates indicate that the United Nations, in partnership with host Governments, currently supports a refugee caseload of approximately 210,000 in the countries neighbouring Iraq. The Department For International Development has provided &#x00A3;1.75 million to UN HCR since the start of the conflict to assist with their work in Iraq and neighbouring countries.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04781'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_249'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-ann-clwyd' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_249' title='Link to this speech by Ms Ann Clwyd' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-ann-clwyd" title="Ms Ann Clwyd">Ann Clwyd</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04781">To ask the Secretary of State for International Development how many internally displaced persons he estimates there are in UN-administered camps in Iraq. [133778]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04782'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_250'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-hilary-benn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_250' title='Link to this speech by Mr Hilary Benn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-hilary-benn" title="Mr Hilary Benn">Hilary Benn</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04782">A recent assessment by the International Organisation for Migration (IOM) places the number of registered internally displaced persons (IDPs) in Iraq at approximately 265,000. The full caseload of people displaced from their homes within Iraq has, however, been estimated at up to one million&#x2014;the vast majority of these are long-term displaced and not as a direct result of the recent conflict. The majority of IDPs are unregistered and are not resident in organised camps.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
